properties.name: region
properties.docs:
The region parameter alters your application to serve different map tiles or bias the application (such as biasing geocoding results towards the region).

Only available for web.

properties.name: language
properties.docs:
The language parameter affects the names of controls, copyright notices, driving directions, and control labels, as well as the responses to service requests.

Only available for web.

satellite, hybrid and terrain modes,
these styles will only apply to labels and geometry.

interfaces.name: Marker
interfaces.docs: A marker is an icon placed at a particular point on the map's surface.

properties.name: coordinate
properties.docs: Marker position

properties.name: opacity
properties.docs: Sets the opacity of the marker, between 0 (completely transparent) and 1 inclusive.

properties.name: title
properties.docs: Title, a short description of the overlay.

properties.name: snippet
properties.docs: Snippet text, shown beneath the title in the info window when selected.

properties.name: isFlat
properties.docs: Controls whether this marker should be flat against the Earth's surface or a billboard facing the camera.

properties.name: iconUrl
properties.docs:
Path to a marker icon to render. It can be relative to the web app public directory,
or a https url of a remote marker icon.

**SVGs are not supported on native platforms.**

properties.name: iconSize
properties.docs: Controls the scaled size of the marker image set in `iconUrl`.

properties.name: iconOrigin
properties.docs: The position of the image within a sprite, if any. By default, the origin is located at the top left corner of the image .

properties.name: iconAnchor
properties.docs: The position at which to anchor an image in correspondence to the location of the marker on the map. By default, the anchor is located along the center point of the bottom of the image.

properties.name: tintColor
properties.docs:
Customizes the color of the default marker image.  Each value must be between 0 and 255.

Only for iOS and Android.
properties.type: { r: number; g: number; b: number; a: number; } | undefined

properties.name: draggable
properties.docs: Controls whether this marker can be dragged interactively

properties.name: zIndex
properties.docs:
Specifies the stack order of this marker, relative to other markers on the map.
A marker with a high z-index is drawn on top of markers with lower z-indexes

interfaces.name: Circle
interfaces.docs:
For web, all the javascript Circle options are available as
Polygon extends google.maps.CircleOptions.
For iOS and Android only the config options declared on Circle are available.

properties.name: fillColor
properties.docs:
The fill color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named
colors.

properties.name: fillOpacity
properties.docs: The fill opacity between 0.0 and 1.0.

properties.name: strokeColor
properties.docs:
The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named
colors.

properties.name: strokeWeight
properties.docs: The stroke width in pixels.

properties.name: clickable
properties.docs: Indicates whether this Circle handles mouse events.

properties.name: title
properties.docs:
Title, a short description of the overlay. Some overlays, such as markers, will display the title on the map. The title is also the default accessibility text.

Only available on iOS.

interfaces.name: Polyline
interfaces.docs:
For web, all the javascript Polyline options are available as
Polyline extends google.maps.PolylineOptions.
For iOS and Android only the config options declared on Polyline are available.

properties.name: strokeColor
properties.docs:
The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named
colors.

properties.name: strokeOpacity
properties.docs: The stroke opacity between 0.0 and 1.0.

properties.name: strokeWeight
properties.docs: The stroke width in pixels.

properties.name: geodesic
properties.docs: When true, edges of the polygon are interpreted as geodesic and will follow the curvature of the Earth. When false, edges of the polygon are rendered as straight lines in screen space. Note that the shape of a geodesic polygon may appear to change when dragged, as the dimensions are maintained relative to the surface of the earth.

properties.name: clickable
properties.docs: Indicates whether this Polyline handles mouse events.

properties.name: styleSpans
properties.docs:
Used to specify the color of one or more segments of a polyline. The styleSpans property is an array of StyleSpan objects.
Setting the spans property is the preferred way to change the color of a polyline.

Only on iOS and Android.

interfaces.name: StyleSpan
interfaces.docs: Describes the style for some region of a polyline.

properties.name: color
properties.docs: The stroke color. All CSS3 colors are supported except for extended named colors.

properties.name: segments
properties.docs: The length of this span in number of segments.

interfaces.name: CameraConfig
interfaces.docs: Configuration properties for a Google Map Camera

properties.name: coordinate
properties.docs: Location on the Earth towards which the camera points.

properties.name: zoom
properties.docs: Sets the zoom of the map.

properties.name: bearing
properties.docs: Bearing of the camera, in degrees clockwise from true north.

properties.name: angle
properties.docs:
The angle, in degrees, of the camera from the nadir (directly facing the Earth).

The only allowed values are 0 and 45.

properties.name: animate
properties.docs: Animate the transition to the new Camera properties.

properties.name: animationDuration
properties.docs: This configuration option is not being used.

typeAliases.name: Position
typeAliases.docs:
A Position is an array of coordinates.
https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7946#section-3.1.1
Array should contain between two and three elements.
The previous GeoJSON specification allowed more elements (e.g., which could be used to represent M values),
but the current specification only allows X, Y, and (optionally) Z to be defined.
